Consider AI specifically: AI-focused data centers are extremely expensive, =
and large training runs benefit from more data rather than less. It is a pr=
etty tall order to build a dedicated European facility for E.U. data alone,=
 which, per Meta=E2=80=99s previous fine, may not even be usable. It makes =
much more sense to have dedicated facilities that can be leveraged across t=
he rest of the world, limiting capital expenditure on one hand and maximizi=
ng data availability on the other.

More broadly, it is the sheer scalability of tech that undergirds the busin=
ess of Aggregators. The reality of zero marginal costs in terms of providin=
g a product, zero marginal costs in terms of distributing content, and zero=
